thout a parser. Barring a 2hander pet damage at 44th would not increase in main hand until I put a 10 damage weapon in both hands. This pushed the damage up to 46's main and 34's off unbuffed. My 49th pet Doubles frequently now for 52's main and 38's off unbuffed, same delay as near as I can tell. It takes two weapons of 12 damage or greater to increase weapon damage (I love Grimling Picks for this, but they aren't magic.. *grr) but only up to 55 and 41. Putting 4 18 Fading/Crystal Shadow Daggers in pets hands did nothing to the damage nor delay that I could tell at 39th, or 49th pet (only tried these). Putting a Sporalli Defender and a Grimling pick in his hands did wonders for the damage output at 67 and 49. His HP's at 39th were around 600-700, at 44th were pretty close to 900-1000 (a 690 nuke and 340 nuke finished him off), and at 49th were fairly close to 1200 as two 690's killed him unbuffed. Regen during battle is between 6 and 10 a tick I would guess since I can see his HP go up while he has Berserker Strength up, and out of battle is enormous likely close to the Mages pet at 49th nearing 30 a tick.<br>
Think I might be doing a few more tests here soon with some of those horribly slow but painful 1handers nobody wants to buy.<br>
Happy Hunting!<br>
